Dialogs.Dialog: Ah... What's up？ Why are you here？
Me？ I'm here just for a change of mood...
I'm here for the same reason...
Hehe. Well... Now that I met you, I feel like today is a nice day.
No, never mind. Well, I have to go. See you later, okay？
Hehe. Are you here for a change of mood again？
Did you come here because you expected to see me... hmm？
No, never mind. Well, see you later, okay？
I wish I could hang out with you a little longer, but...
Yeah, I have to go home now. Sorry. Bye...
Ah... Hehe. You also come to this place.
Did you come to watch a movie alone？
▲姉ヶ崎＊▲, too？ Did you watch a movie alone？
Did I... ask a weird question？
No, you didn't. It's just... I was thinking that I should've invited you here.
Hehe. It's okay. We can come here together next time, all right？
We meet again. Are you here by yourself？
Yeah, but I just got out of the theater and I'm about to go home...
I see. Too bad. We couldn't watch it together.
Don't worry. We can come here together next time, right？
Ah, we run into each other again...？
Hehe. I'm not sure if we should call this good or bad timing.
It's okay. Don't worry. We can come here together later whenever we want.
...Hehe. I found this cute boy right here.
Hehe. I see... That's good. It's good that you're training your body, but don't forget about me, okay？
Hehe. Now, I've got to go...
You don't have to concern about me. Are you possibly trying to get brawny？
I object！ I don't want you to be brawny！ So, don't！
Ah, ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲. You're here again... Are you possibly trying to lose weight？
It's okay that you enjoy body training, but...
Don't ever talk to your girlfriend about her weight！ This is the warning！
Perhaps, you're buying presents for some other girls？
Geez... You don't have to fluster like that...
Fine, I trust you... Sorry that I said something weird...
Ah, I have to go... See you later, okay？
I have to get going... Hehe. It feels nice that we met like this, right？
Ah... We often meet here. Are you shopping？
Got so much free time, huh？
No, I also have a lot of things to take care of.
I see. I want to hang out with you a little more, but I have to go now. Bye.
Could it be that... there are some posters of the idols you like at the entrance？
It's fine. I'm a very understanding girlfriend.
I know. You're at the age that would be interested in something like that.
It's fine. I understand. If I'm still your "number one," I wouldn't mind if you also look at some other girls.
(No good. She's not listening to me...)
Let me tell you first. I'm not attending any weird event...
Huh？ It sounds even more suspicious when you say that.
Hehe. I'll trust you this time. I don't want to be an evil woman. Well, I have to go...
Hehe. If you like it this much, how about we come here together for a date next time？
Think about it, okay？ Ah, I have to run an errand. ...See you later.
Hey！ What are you doing at the game center！
A student's duty is to study, right？ Do you have so much time to play around！？
Just kidding. Hehe. I just wanted to act like a big sister.
I've wanted to say this for a long time. “Don't play. Go to study！” Something like that.
I'll let you off this time, but you should go home before it gets dark, okay？
Hehe. Guys really like to come to this place, huh？
Hehe, I have to go now. Don't play until you forget your girlfriend, okay？
Hey, that boy. Do you want to play with this big sister？
Too bad. This big sister is too busy today, so she can't play with you. Bye now！
Mister, what are you looking for？
Hehe. I've wanted to say it. That line isn't what we use to greet customers at a family restaurant, right？
I'm... just checking the prices, okay？
Hehe. Don't cause any trouble, okay？
Yeah, very well. I have an errand to run, so I'm leaving. Bye.
Mister, have you found what you were looking for？
Hehe. We meet again. How's that？ Is my service outside the family restaurant okay？
▲姉ヶ崎＊▲, with your manners, you can work at any place.
Hehe. Even if you're trying to flatter me, I can't cut the price for you, okay？
(So, she still enjoys playing as a shopkeeper, huh...？)
By the way, you still haven't told me what you were looking for...
We met here a lot. Do you like this store that much？
I didn't plan to come here. I was just walking aimlessly and somehow I ended up here.
Hehe. I see. Too bad I already have my plans. I have to go now. See you later, okay？
Ah, I didn't expect to see you here. Are you looking for something？
I know that. This store only sells CDs.
What？ Do you have a problem with me？
All right. I'll forgive you. Hehe.
Hehe. It's because you're so cute, you know？
Hehe. This time, shall I show you my favorite CDs？
And then... If you think of me while you're listening to them, I'll be happy.
What？ It's the Music Boy again？
▲姉ヶ崎＊▲... I'm not a Music Boy.
I think guys who are interested in various things are wonderful, you know？
Yes, yes. Hehe, do your best, okay？
(And what am I supposed to do my best for？)
▲姉ヶ崎＊▲. What's up？ Why are you here？
Well, the promotional items for my favorite movie are out today, but I can't find them.
Every once in a while, you try to show me how reliable you are, huh？
Hehe. Just kidding. Please help me▼
▲姉ヶ崎＊▲, what a coincidence. Are you looking for some movie related items again？
Yeah, that's right... Can you accompany me for a while？
Thanks. ...Hey, you come here a lot, huh？
Really. You come here a lot, huh...？
I'm here for some errands, but what about you？ What are you doing here？
Today is totally a coincidence. I only come here occasionally...
Yeah. Ah, I have to get going now.
This place is a maid cafe, right？
Perhaps, you like this place more than a family restaurant, huh？
No. I saw you from afar, so I followed you.
Hehe. Just kidding. Did I surprise you？
Ahaha. Did I scare you？ So cute▼
Hey, don't make fun of me.
